  "title": "Clinic Assistant #82101",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Medical and dental practice activities</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Clinic Assistant</strong></li><li>Working Location: Farrer Park</li><li>Working Hours: 5 days (Monday – Friday, 8:00 AM – 5:00 PM)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic Salary + Performance Bonus + Medical Benefits</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent Role</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Greet and register patients, schedule appointments, and manage walk-in patients efficiently.</li><li>Assist doctors during consultations and minor procedures.</li><li>Prepare consultation rooms and ensure they are clean and ready before and after each patient.</li><li>Dispense medication accurately according to prescriptions, with proper labelling and instructions.</li><li>Collect payments and issue receipts, and support claims and billing where needed (e.g., Medisave, CHAS, insurance portals).</li><li>Maintain accurate patient records and update the clinic management system.</li><li>Carry out basic clinical tasks such as taking vital signs (height, weight, blood pressure, etc.), if trained.</li><li>Manage clinic supplies, inventory, and stock replenishment.</li><li>Ensure the clinic is always clean and safe.</li><li>Handle incoming calls and general enquiries professionally.</li><li>Provide administrative support and assist with other ad-hoc duties as assigned.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum GCE ‘O’ Level or a relevant certificate in healthcare support or administration.</li><li>At least 2 years of relevant experience in an outpatient clinic/GP setting.</li><li>Able to multitask, work in a fast-paced environment, and handle patients with care and professionalism.</li><li>Basic knowledge of Microsoft Office and clinic management systems is preferred.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#82101 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
